RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WORK IT dueled for command from outside, shook free around the bend, widened in the lane and was ridden out to the wire. SCREAMING VIRGINIA sat off the pace, went two wide into the turn, eased out to entered the lane four wide, showed a mild response when asked and held the place. PLEASEUSETHEPORTAL chased at the back early, trailed on the inside into the turn, steered out exiting the bend, rallied and missed the place. PHAROAHS LIST stalked off the rail, rounded the bend three wide and flattened out. DETAILS MATTER dueled from inside into and around the bend, failed to kick on with the winner late on the turn, came out in the lane and weakened. DAWSON broke a step slow, got shuffled back early, moved up into range stalking from inside and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Details Matter
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled inside, came out stretch, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Work It
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled outside, shook free, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Dawson
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, crowded early, stalked inside, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Pleaseusetheportal
ENTRY.OWNER: Alvernaz Grant Haymes Neil A Nigro Louis and Ribeiro Steven A
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, inside, angled out, missed 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROSE GIRL broke out and brushed ZZYZX, set the pace on the inside then two wide into the lane, asked right-handed at the three-sixteenths pole and edged away. BELLA BABY broke out, chased two wide into the turn, took aim three wide into the stretch, could not summon the needed late kick in the final furlong but was clearly second best. ZZYZX got brushed from inside at the start, tracked three then four wide around the bend, churned on down the lane and finished a clear third. PARCO coaxed from the gate, chased a bit off the rail then two wide into the stretch and flattened in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Rose Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out/brushed, pace inside-2wide, edged away

ENTRY.NAME: Zzyzx
ENTRY.OWNER: Baker Connie Baker Jerry Parsons Anthony and Parsons Rachel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROAD OF LOVE broke well and dueled for a bit but could not keep up early with MY BROTHER MIKE, chased that rival in the two path through the turn, drew alongside past the quarter pole, cleared at the three-sixteenths pole and held well under urging. BLUEGRASS RYDER tracked near the inside then switched out, rounded the bend three wide, finished willingly through the lane but had to settle for second best. MY BROTHER MIKE dueled from outside then cleared past the nine-sixteenths pole and crossed over, set the pace along the inside to the stretch, challenged at the top of the lane, relinquished the lead to ROAD OF LOVE, flattened in the furlong grounds but managed to save the show. ACCELERAY chased three to four wide around the turn and lacked a rally. NUMBER ONE SON chased four wide into the turn, angled down to the inside around the bend and lacked further response. RANGER JOE was off slow and lost his path at the start, became hard to ride trailing the field, continued to fight the rider in upper stretch and never got involved.

ENTRY.NAME: Bluegrass Ryder
ENTRY.OWNER: Pinkerton Mary Lee and Warren John P

ENTRY.NAME: Ranger Joe
ENTRY.OWNER: Bamford Alice De Seroux Laura Dugan Shawn L and Naify Marsha
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow/lost path, hard to ride

ENTRY.NAME: Acceleray
ENTRY.OWNER: Gans Doug Jacobs Gary Katz Larry Riggs Kevin and Wright Robert

ENTRY.NAME: Road of Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, chased 2wide, cleared, held well

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 21000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INDY'S STAR stalked the leaders up the backstretch, went two to three wide on the turn, angled out and came five wide into the stretch, bid outside the top pair, took over midstretch and won going away. A NEW PEACE chased four wide into the turn, coaxed along while wide through the turn, exited the bend seven wide and rallied to get up for second. GAYLES EVENING dueled inside LASTING LOVE for the lead, fought along the rail then two wide on the turn, drifted out a bit into the lane, fought into the final furlong and got edged for the place. LASTING LOVE dueled outside GAYLES EVENING, battled two then three wide around the turn, drifted out a bit into the lane, fought to the eighth pole and weakened. ALOHA KITTEN sat off the pace along the inside into the turn, moved out to the three path around the bend, entered the lane two wide and failed to menace. FLAT OUT JOY raced up close from outside, rounded the bend three then four wide, came five wide into the stretch and weakened.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Brandywine Farm (Jim & Pam Robinson) & Parker Place Breedi

ENTRY.NAME: A New Peace
ENTRY.OWNER: Jimmy Rex Robinson Family Trust Exelby Randy and Mayo Tom
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased off rail, 7wide into str, up for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Flat Out Joy
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close outside, 3-4wide, 5wide into str, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 17000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROJECT LEADER stepped to the front from inside, showed the way two wide then along the inside on the turn, put to right handed urging in upper stretch and held well. HANDR'SDREAM bumped leaving the gate, forwardly placed up the backstretch, navigated the turn two wide, chased after the winner willingly down the lane but could not summon the needed late kick. NOLONGERAHOBBY tracked off the rail, came four wide into the lane and was along for the show. EQUIPO A raced up close from outside, rounded the turn four then three wide and flattened in the lane. MY MAN BAGS got bumped leaving the gate, forwardly placed four wide into the first turn, exited the bend three wide and weakened. DEBT MONGER got brushed and put in a bit tight at the start, stalked from inside through the turn and weakened.

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: George Schmitt, Mary Clare Schmitt & Richard Meister

ENTRY.NAME: Debt Monger
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed/bit tight start, stalked inside, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 100. Starter Allowance Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SO I'M TOLD away quickly at the start, dueled inside SOUL OF MIDNIGHT, put away that rival past the three-eighths pole, came off the rail to show the way three wide into the lane and held safely. GALOPING CAT stalked the pace from inside, saved ground through the turn, moved off the rail in the lane and outfinished THE KEY IS UNITY for second. THE KEY IS UNITY chased five to six wide on the turn, chased outside GALOPING CAT down the lane and got outkicked for the place honors. SOUL OF MIDNIGHT bumped at the start, dueled outside SO I'M TOLD to the turn, failed to go on with that rival past the three-eighths pole, exited the bend four wide and weakened. TIGER'S ARROW bumped SOUL OF MIDNIGHT, chased four then five wide before angling down to the three path on the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: So I'm Told
ENTRY.OWNER: Mojarro Racing LLC and Carlos Felipe
ENTRY.COMMENT: away quickly, dueled inside, 2-3wide, cleared turn, held safely

ENTRY.NAME: The Key Is Unity
ENTRY.OWNER: Zepeda Racing Inc and Glassman Richard L

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 21000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED CROSS KNIGHT raced up close outside the top pair, chased three wide through the turn, bid between at the top of the stretch, dueled with PERFECT D in the final furlong and dug in late to prevail. PERFECT D brushed leaving the gate, showed speed then was taken in hand and raced keenly, looked to make a run on the turn but lacked room in traffic, tipped out and bid three wide at the top of the lane, took over shortly after, dueled with RED CROSS KNIGHT in the furlong grounds and finished gamely in defeat. MIDNIGHT SPECIAL chased four deep into the turn, remained four wide into the lane, offered a challenge in upper stretch and flattened to third. DR. TROUTMAN broke a step slow, went up to duel from inside into and around the bend, could not kick on with the leaders at the top of the stretch, churned on while moving off the inside and earned a minor award. DIVINE FEMININE took a bump from inside, chased three wide into the turn, angled five wide into the drive and lacked a rally. FAST PER SE away quickest while brushing outer rival, dueled outside DR. TROUTMAN, inched ahead around the bend, cleared inner rival into the stretch but was soon challenged at the quarter pole from outer rivals and weakened once overtaken. TEMBO broke out and bumped, trailed five wide into the turn, six wide into the lane and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Tembo
ENTRY.OWNER: Tomasic Susan and Tomasic William J

ENTRY.NAME: Perfect D
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed start, keen, traffic turn, bid 3wide, led, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Red Cross Knight
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close 3deep, bid between, dueled, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Special
ENTRY.OWNER: Sides Clay R and Valenzuela Jr Martin
